        "title": "6d. `fetch_source` / `fetch_all` (dispatch + fault isolation)",
        "content": "\nGaps:\n- `fetch_source` raises `ValueError` on unknown `ats`, listing known ones.\n- `fetch_all`: one source failing doesn't kill the whole batch (`except Exception` per-source).\n- `fetch_all` closes an owned client but not an injected one (`owns_client` logic).\n- Concurrency semaphore actually caps in-flight requests (harder to test directly — can assert via a counter + `asyncio.Event`).\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nfrom fetchers import fetch_source, fetch_all\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchSource:\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises_value_error(self):\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(None, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchAll:\n    async def test_one_source_failure_does_not_abort_others(self):\n        async def fake_dispatch(client, src):\n            if src[\"company\"] == \"bad\":\n                raise RuntimeError(\"boom\")\n            return [AsyncMock()]\n        with patch(\"fetchers.fetch_source\", side_effect=fake_dispatch):\n            results = await fetch_all(\n                [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"bad\"},\n                 {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"good\"}])\n        assert len(results) == 1  # only \"good\" contributed\n\n    async def test_closes_owned_client_not_injected_client(self):\n        import httpx\n        injected = httpx.AsyncClient()\n        with patch(\"fetchers.fetch_source\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[])):\n            await fetch_all([], client=injected)\n        assert not injected.is_closed\n        await injected.aclose()\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
