        "title": "8. `cli.py`",
        "content": "\n**Untested:** `main` — argparse wiring only, low risk but still zero coverage.\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom cli import main\n\nclass TestCli:\n    def test_default_config_path(self):\n        with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as run_sync, patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\"]):\n            main()\n        run_sync.assert_called_once_with(\"sources.yaml\", dry_run=False)\n\n    def test_dry_run_flag_passed_through(self):\n        with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as run_sync, \\\n             patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"--dry-run\"]):\n            main()\n        run_sync.assert_called_once_with(\"sources.yaml\", dry_run=True)\n```\n\n---\n\n",
