        "title": "9. Integration test gaps (no fetcher-to-notify path is exercised end-to-end today)",
        "content": "\n- **Full pipeline run**: fake `httpx.MockTransport` serving canned Greenhouse/Lever payloads → `run()` → assert `Store` has the right rows and `notify_console` printed the right lines. Currently every layer is tested (once the above exists) only in isolation; nothing proves they compose correctly.\n- **Re-run idempotency**: run the pipeline twice against the same fixture data → second run reports `new=0`.\n- **Content-change propagation**: run once, mutate a fixture job's title, run again → job appears in `changed`, not `new`, and a notifier receives it.\n- **`agent.py db-new` → `db-mark` cycle**: run pipeline (seeds DB) → `db-new` dumps rows → `db-mark <watermark>` → second `db-new` call returns nothing until new rows land after the watermark.\n- **Notifier fan-out on a real dispatch**: assert that a Slack-webhook failure doesn't prevent the SMS notifier (later in `NOTIFIERS` list) from firing.\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nimport httpx\nfrom pipeline import run\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestPipelineIntegration:\n    async def test_rerun_reports_zero_new(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"\"\"\nsources:\n  - ats: greenhouse\n    company: acme\ndb: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\n\"\"\")\n        with respx.mock:\n            respx.get(\"https://boards-api.greenhouse.io/v1/boards/acme/jobs\").mock(\n                return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [\n                    {\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\", \"absolute_url\": \"https://x/1\"}]}))\n            first = await run(cfg)\n            second = await run(cfg)\n        assert first[\"new\"] == 1\n        assert second[\"new\"] == 0\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 2
