      {
        "title": "Priority order if resourcing is limited",
        "content": "1. **`filters.py` + `models.py`** — pure functions, cheapest to test, and the `cutoff`-keeps-unparseable-dates behavior in `match()` is a real correctness trap for anyone modifying it later.\n2. **`fetchers.py` parse_* functions** — pure, high fan-out (14 ATS integrations), most likely to silently break when an external API reshapes its payload.\n3. **`store.py` diff logic** — the dedup/change-detection is the core value proposition of the whole tool; a bug here means duplicate notifications or silently dropped listings.\n4. **`notify.py`** — env-var gating bugs here mean either notification spam or total silence, and nothing today would catch it.\n5. **Pagination fetchers + retry wrapper** — needs `respx`, more setup cost, but this is where real-world flakiness (rate limits, layout drift) lives.\n6. **`agent.py`** — lower risk (mostly glue + one regex normalizer), but `cmd_db_new`'s group-boundary truncation logic is subtle enough to deserve a regression test.",
        "level": 2
      }
    ],
